{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"68bc12f1-4e47-47f3-9c64-61a0ea3920cf","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet --version` to confirm the SDK, then `dotnet build` to check for any breaking API changes. Review the [Microsoft .NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for any additional breaking changes relevant to your dependencies.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5807b911-c245-4bb6-bd79-e378d4623de1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":268,"requestId":"6C20:1EB7C4:DE2BC5:105E461:69FE9333"},"id":"31487c03-33a9-490a-8141-a3a989c3db4e","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:51:53.295Z","parentId":"c36dd24f-6392-4f9a-bca9-baa8c1cd3aa1"}
